Charles Mizzi is the CEO of the Residency Malta Agency – a government entity responsible for managing and promoting the Malta Permanent Residence Programme. Mizzi graduated with a Master’s Degree in Business Administration from the Henley Business School, and began his career in the banking sector, where he held several roles in marketing and business development. In 2014, he was appointed as the Executive Director of Media and Marketing for the Maltese Presidency in the European Council. He then became the Chief Officer for Communications and Business Development at the Individual Investor Programme Agency in 2017, before being appointed as the CEO of Residency Malta Agency in 2019. In this episode of Business Talk, Mizzi explains why Malta is a great second residency option for South Africans. He outlines the requirements South Africans must meet to become a resident of Malta and explains how the Residency Malta Agency makes the process simple. Mizzi also discusses interesting trends he is seeing in terms of the people applying for residency in the European country. He then details the next steps for anyone who is interested in becoming a Maltese resident and concludes by explaining the benefit of working remotely in a country like Malta while serving customers in another nation. Watch the full Business Talk interview with Charles Mizzi below, and click here to learn more about becoming a Maltese resident. 